---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Contact Arcanum — Questions, Collaboration & Support"
  description="Get in touch with Arcanum. Questions about the games, setup help, collaboration enquiries, or anything else — one inbox, we read everything."
>
  <article class="wrap contact">
    <p class="eyebrow mono">// contact</p>
    <h1>Contact Arcanum</h1>

    <div class="body">
      <p class="lede">One inbox. No forms. We read everything.</p>

      <p>Write to us at <a href="mailto:rukkagamer@gmail.com">rukkagamer@gmail.com</a> — for anything. Response time is usually within a few days.</p>

      <p class="email mono"><a href="mailto:rukkagamer@gmail.com">rukkagamer@gmail.com</a></p>

      <h2>What We Can Help With</h2>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Setup questions</strong> — if you're having trouble loading a game into ChatGPT, Claude, or Gemini, describe what you're seeing and we'll walk you through it.</li>
        <li><strong>Game questions</strong> — anything about how a specific mechanic works, what a command does, or how a system is designed.</li>
        <li><strong>Collaboration and press</strong> — if you write about AI RPGs, run a community, or want to cover what we're building, get in touch.</li>
        <li><strong>Privacy and data requests</strong> — access, deletion, or any other request under GDPR. See our <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a> for what we collect and how.</li>
        <li><strong>Anything else</strong> — if a campaign went well, that's worth hearing too.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Looking for Something Specific?</h2>

      <p>If you're not sure where to start, here are the most useful places on the site:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><a href="/arcanum-games">Arcanum Originals</a> — download the game files and read setup instructions for each engine.</li>
        <li><a href="/blog/why-llms-forget">Why AI campaigns fall apart at turn 50</a> — the guide to keeping a long AI RPG coherent.</li>
        <li><a href="/clients">Client directory</a> — honest comparisons of every major AI roleplay platform.</li>
        <li><a href="/blog">The Codex</a> — all our guides, reviews, and articles in one place.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>

  <style>
    .contact { padding: 4rem 1.25rem 5rem; max-width: 780px; }
    .eyebrow { color: var(--rune); font-size: .8rem; letter-spacing: .05em; margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
    h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .lede { font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--parchment); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .body p { color: var(--parchment-dim); margin-bottom: 1.4rem; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 1.05rem; }
    .email { font-size: 1.1rem; margin: .4rem 0 2.4rem; }
    .email a { color: var(--ember); letter-spacing: .02em; }
    .body h2 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin: 2.2rem 0 .8rem; color: var(--parchment); }
    .body ul { padding-left: 1.4rem; margin-bottom: 1.4rem; }
    .body li { color: var(--parchment-dim); margin-bottom: .6rem; line-height: 1.7; font-size: 1.05rem; }
    .body li strong { color: var(--parchment); }
  </style>
</Base>
